The character who had a childhood dream of playing for the **Brooklyn Dodgers** (not the New York Dodgers) was **Terence Mann**.

This detail is revealed when Ray Kinsella reads a magazine interview about Mann’s past, which inspires Ray to seek him out. The confusion about the team name (Brooklyn Dodgers vs. New York Dodgers) reflects the timeline shift in the story, as the Dodgers relocated from Brooklyn to Los Angeles in 1958.

